articular to institutionalized racial inequality as the fundamental principle of government during the past century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aAIDS (Disease)xGovernment policyxSouth Africa. 0aAIDS (Disease)xGovernment policyzSouth Africa. 0aAIDS (Disease)xPolitical aspectsxSouth Africa. 0aAIDS (Disease)xPolitical aspectszSouth Africa. 0aAIDS (Disease)xSocial aspectsxSouth Africa. 0aAIDS (Disease)xSocial aspectszSouth Africa. 0aAIDS (Disease). 0aEthnology. 0aHIV infections. 0aMedical policy. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh  aaids epidemic.  aaids.  aanc government.  aanthropology.  aapartheid.  acolonial period.  acolonialism.  ademographic studies.  adissidents.  aepidemiology.  aethnography.  agenocide.  aglobal aids crisis.  aglobal controversy.  agovernment and governing.  ahealth.  ahiv.  ahuman tragedy.  ajohannesburg.  amedical anthropology.  amedical research.  amedical.  amother to child transmission.  apolitical.  apolitics.  apresident thabo mbeki.  aquestionable medical research.  arace theory.  aracial inequality.  asocial history.  asouth africa.  asouth african history.  aviral theory.1 aF., D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094045140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520940451423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520940451/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles